The paper deals with codes and their properties in the context of multimedia fingerprinting, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The identifiable parent property (IPP) is a concept from cryptography and security (cs.CR), and the paper also uses combinatorial techniques (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.SI) to derive bounds and construct codes.
